author: Eliot Shorr-Parks | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: Sam Bradford, DeMarco Murray among 'Studs & Duds' from Eagles' win over Saints
text:
For one day, everything went to plan.
With 39 points and 519 yards of offense, the 2015 Eagles -- or at least the team that was supposed to be the 2015 Eagles -- finally showed up Sunday in a 39-17 win over the New Orleans Saints.
They finally ran the ball, to the tune of 186 yards on the ground. They passed the ball, gaining 333 yards through the air while having nine players catch at least one pass.
BRADFORD: Report card from win over Saints The complete game, or at least the closest the team has played to a complete game this season, improved the Eagles to 2-3, only one game out of first place in the NFC East.
So who showed up -- and who still needs to do a better job?
Check out the gallery above for the studs and the duds from the Eagles' big win.
